# Gnosys Memory System

You have access to persistent memory via Gnosys MCP tools. Use them proactively.

## Retrieve memories

- At the start of every task, call `gnosys_discover` with keywords for what you're working on
- Call `gnosys_read` to load any relevant results
- Trigger on: "remember when…", "what did we decide…", "recall", "check your memory", "do we have notes on…"
- Use `gnosys_hybrid_search` for best search results, `gnosys_ask` for Q&A with citations

## Write memories

- Trigger on: "remember this", "memorize", "save this", "note this down", "store this", "don't forget"
- Also write when the user states a decision, preference, or opinion — even casually
- Commit specs and plans BEFORE starting implementation
- After significant work, commit findings (gotchas, what worked, what didn't)

## Tools

- `gnosys_add` — write memory from freeform text (LLM structures it)
- `gnosys_add_structured` — write with explicit title, category, content, tags, relevance
- `gnosys_update` — modify existing memory
- `gnosys_reinforce` — signal useful / not_relevant / outdated
- `gnosys_commit_context` — extract novel memories from a conversation context
- `gnosys_discover` — lightweight metadata search (call FIRST)
- `gnosys_read` — load full memory content
- `gnosys_search` — keyword search
- `gnosys_hybrid_search` — keyword + semantic (best results)
- `gnosys_ask` — natural-language Q&A with citations
- `gnosys_list` — list all memories
- `gnosys_lens` — filtered view (category, tag, status, confidence, date)
- `gnosys_tags` / `gnosys_tags_add` — tag registry
- `gnosys_links` / `gnosys_graph` — wikilink relationships
- `gnosys_history` / `gnosys_rollback` — version control
- `gnosys_stats` / `gnosys_dashboard` — system overview
- `gnosys_maintain` — vault maintenance (dedup, decay, consolidation)
- `gnosys_stale` — find memories not updated recently
- `gnosys_stores` — show active store layers
- `gnosys_init` — initialize a new store
- `gnosys_bootstrap` / `gnosys_import` — bulk import
- `gnosys_reindex` / `gnosys_reindex_graph` — rebuild indexes

## Categories

Use these when writing: `architecture`, `decisions`, `requirements`, `concepts`, `roadmap`, `landscape`, `open-questions`
